04411nam a22006015i 9780226407739DE-B159720200424112023.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||200424t20162016ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802264077397 a10.7208/97802264077392doi  a(DE-B1597)523909  a(OCoLC)960458140  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL 4aML3917.I4bN37 2017 7aMUS0000002bisacsh04a782.421629141100822231 aNarayan, Kirin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aEveryday Creativity :bSinging Goddesses in the Himalayan Foothills /cKirin Narayan. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2016] 4c©2016  a1 online resource (256 p.) :b9 halftones  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBig Issues in Music00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tForeword: Todi in the Forest of Song -- tFinding Form -- t1. Tending Lives through Songs -- t2. The Ground That Grows Songs -- t3. Attaining: The Mountain Daughter's Many Forms -- t4. Playing: Krishna's Mothers, Sister, and Lovers -- t5. Going: Saili as Plant and Goddess -- t6. Bathing: The Transformative Flows of Sound -- tReaching the Head -- tA Note on Transliteration -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aKirin Narayan's imagination was captured the very first time that, as a girl visiting the Himalayas, she heard Kangra women join their voices together in song. Returning as an anthropologist, she became fascinated by how they spoke of singing as a form of enrichment, bringing feelings of accomplishment, companionship, happiness, and even good health-all benefits of the "everyday creativity" she explores in this book. Part ethnography, part musical discovery, part poetry, part memoir, and part unforgettable portraits of creative individuals, this unique work brings this remote region in North India alive in sight and sound while celebrating the incredible powers of music in our lives. With rare and captivating eloquence, Narayan portrays Kangra songs about difficulties on the lives of goddesses and female saints as a path to well-being. Like the intricate geometries of mandalu patterns drawn in courtyards or the subtle balance of flavors in a meal, well-crafted songs offer a variety of deeply meaningful benefits: as a way of making something of value, as a means of establishing a community of shared pleasure and skill, as a path through hardships and limitations, and as an arena of renewed possibility. Everyday Creativity makes big the small world of Kangra song and opens up new ways of thinking about what creativity is to us and why we are so compelled to engage it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aMusicxSocial aspectszIndiazKāngra (District) 0aMusicxSocial aspectszIndiazKāngra (District). 0aWomen singerszIndiazKāngra (District) 0aWomen singerszIndiazKāngra (District). 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh1 aBohlman, Philip V.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2014-2016z978311070422808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2016z978311068860308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226407739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226407739.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-068860-3  UChP eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070422-8  UChP eBook-Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles